1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper is primarily concerned with statistical learning problems and proposes a method to solve constrained statistical problems using finite dimensional parameterizations and duality theory. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the challenge of selecting regularization parameters to satisfy constraints and proposes a method to overcome this challenge using sample averages. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to incorporate prior knowledge and impose desired structural and statistical properties on solutions, which is relevant to the field of AI. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the challenge of solving constrained statistical problems and proposes a method to make the problem tractable, which is relevant to the field of algorithms. 
5. cs.ST (Statistics): The paper is concerned with statistical learning problems and proposes a method to solve constrained statistical problems, which is relevant to the field of statistics.
